Psalm 63

2 O Gód, you are my Gód; at dawn I séek you;
for yóu my sóul is thirsting.
For yóu my flésh is píning,
like a drý, weary lánd without wáter.
3 I have cóme before yóu in the sánctuary,
to behóld your stréngth and your glóry.

4 Your loving mércy is bétter than lífe;
my líps will spéak your práise.
5 I will bléss you áll my lífe;
in your náme I will líft up my hánds.
6 My sóul shall be fílled as with a bánquet;
with joyful líps, my móuth shall práise you.

7 When I remémber you upón my béd,
I muse on yóu through the wátches of the níght.
8 For yóu have béen my stréngth;
in the shádow of your wíngs I rejóice.
9 My sóul clings fást to yóu;
yóur right hánd uphólds me.

10 Those who séek to destróy my lífe
shall go dówn to the dépths of the éarth.
11 Pút to the pówer of the swórd,
they shall be léft as préy for the jáckals.

12 But the kíng shall rejóice in Gód;
all that swéar by hím shall exúlt,
for the móuth of líars shall be sílenced.
